{
  "doc_id": "13018",
  "text": "Differently, Cu 2+ stimulated about 12.7% and 31.5% the activity of Lacps1, at concentrations of 1 and 5 mmol¨L´1, respectively. Similarly to our results, stimulation by Cu 2+ has been described for two laccases from Pycnoporus sp. SYBC-L1 [CITATION_1] , as well as for the laccases from some other white-rot fungi [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The stimulation by Cu 2+ has been attributed to the filling of the T2 copper sites on the enzyme molecules [CITATION_5] . However, some Cu 2+ -inhibited laccases have also been described [CITATION_6] .",
